HEADWORD: Sphagnum
<hw>Sphag"num</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr/ Gr.
<?/<?/<?/ a kind of moss.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of
mosses having white leaves slightly tinged with red or green and found
growing in marshy places; bog moss; peat moss.</def>⟦br⟧
